olive oil
1 packet basmati rice
1 carrot
1 bag broccoli florets
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet curry powder
1 packet peanut butter
1 packet coconut milk
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tbs brown sugar
¼ cup water
1 tsp white wine vinegar

• Boil the kettle.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12 minutes.
• Drain and set aside.

• Meanwhile, slice carrot into half-moons. Cut any larger broccoli florets in half.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook broccoli and carrot, tossing, until tender, 6-8 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging.
• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate.
• Return the frying pan to medium heat, then add curry powder, peanut butter, coconut milk, chicken-style stock powder, the soy sauce, brown sugar and the water. Simmer, stirring, until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then return veggies and beef to the pan with a drizzle of white wine vinegar, and stir to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide rapid rice between bowls. Top with satay beef and veggie curry. Enjoy!